{
  "text": "The management of patellofemoral instability is multifaceted, with an extensive number of treatment options available [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Sound mechanical osseous alignment with balance of the associated soft-tissue structures are integral components to management when a surgical procedure is required. Surgical intervention involves assessment of the severity of instability and the underlying etiological factors to formulate a patientspecific management plan [CITATION_5] 14 . A greater understanding of the role of the rotational alignment of the quadriceps muscles may help to differentiate patients requiring more aggressive softtissue management of their pathology.",
  "correct_citation": {
